WEBVTT

00:01.479 --> 00:01.697
.

00:01.740 --> 00:04.308
- Previously on
"Good Girls"...

00:04.352 --> 00:05.831
- Why does a grocery store
even have this kind of money?

00:05.875 --> 00:07.355
- Because it's hella shady!

00:07.398 --> 00:09.009
- Call your friends over
so we can have a little talk.

00:09.052 --> 00:10.749
- He wants us to pick something
up for him in Canada.

00:10.793 --> 00:12.534
It's just wrapping paper.

00:12.577 --> 00:16.190
We have a business proposition
to clean your fake money.

00:16.233 --> 00:19.280
- What are you proposing?
- Let us do it, right here.

00:19.323 --> 00:21.021
Fake money in, real money out.

00:21.064 --> 00:22.370
- [whispering]
What do you want?

00:22.413 --> 00:25.286
You can't just walk in here.
- Door was open.

00:25.329 --> 00:27.418
- Beth, who's your new friend?

00:27.462 --> 00:29.072
Is he the reason
you're not wearing your ring?

00:29.116 --> 00:31.031
- Oh, my God.
I want you out.

00:31.074 --> 00:33.076
- What?
- Yeah, I want you gone now.

00:33.120 --> 00:34.991
- I have cancer.

00:35.035 --> 00:37.037
- Agent Turner, I saw this guy.

00:37.080 --> 00:38.908
Okay, he was with
the three of them before,

00:38.951 --> 00:40.344
And I saw him again yesterday.

00:40.388 --> 00:43.260
Whatever they're into,
he is involved.

00:43.304 --> 00:45.349
- Hi, I'm looking
for Mrs. Boland.

00:45.393 --> 00:49.136
- Can I help you?
- I'm hoping you can.

00:50.224 --> 00:53.009
- Cute kids.
- Aw, thanks, we like them.

00:53.053 --> 00:54.663
Yeah, most of the time.

00:54.706 --> 00:56.273
- And how's the
neighborhood treating you?

00:56.317 --> 00:59.407
Pretty quiet, mostly, or?
- Is something going on?

00:59.450 --> 01:01.713
- Oh, just some ugliness
bleeding in from the city.

01:01.757 --> 01:04.455
We try to stay on top of it.
- Well, that sounds scary.

01:04.499 --> 01:07.067
- Yeah, you guys
seen anything weird?

01:07.110 --> 01:08.155
- Like what?

01:08.198 --> 01:09.286
- You know, people that don't

01:09.330 --> 01:12.202
quite go with the vibe here.

01:12.246 --> 01:14.335
- Actually, I have.

01:14.378 --> 01:18.513
That guy, the, um,
the--the guy.

01:18.556 --> 01:20.906
Question, is it illegal
to throw dog poop

01:20.950 --> 01:22.386
into other people's trash bins?

01:22.430 --> 01:25.911
Because we have this guy
in the neighborhood, who, uh--

01:25.955 --> 01:27.913
it's probably not
FBI jurisdiction.

01:27.957 --> 01:29.350
- I'm guessing not.

01:29.393 --> 01:31.526
- Those are
government bins, right?

01:31.569 --> 01:33.658
So...
- [chuckles]

01:33.702 --> 01:37.227
Let me know if you see
anything out of the ordinary.

01:37.271 --> 01:39.490
- Copy that, we will
be your eyes and ears.

01:39.534 --> 01:43.581
- Yes.
And thank you, Agent Turner.

01:43.625 --> 01:46.193
- Jimmy.

01:46.236 --> 01:48.151
- Yeah, I'll show you out.

01:48.195 --> 01:50.588
So yeah, this guy,
he walks his dog,

01:50.632 --> 01:54.157
and he's like a great Dane...
- Mm-hmm.

01:54.201 --> 01:57.160
[dramatic music]

01:57.204 --> 01:59.771
♪

01:59.815 --> 02:01.208
- We shouldn't do it.

02:01.251 --> 02:02.818
- What do you mean
we shouldn't do it?

02:02.861 --> 02:05.255
- I mean we shouldn't clean
a bunch of counterfeit money

02:05.299 --> 02:06.735
when the FBI is on our trail.

02:06.778 --> 02:08.040
- It was your idea!

02:08.084 --> 02:09.955
- Can you all
keep it down please?

02:09.999 --> 02:11.957
- Look, they're not
on our trail, okay?

02:12.001 --> 02:14.612
- He was in my kitchen.
- Stan is in my bedroom.

02:14.656 --> 02:16.745
- If the guy knew anything,
he would have just said it.

02:16.788 --> 02:20.227
- He gave his card to me,
and not to Dean.

02:20.270 --> 02:23.665
- Well, maybe he didn't know
if Dean could read.

02:23.708 --> 02:25.275
Look, I got
fancy lawyer bills

02:25.319 --> 02:26.972
coming out
the wazoo, dawg!

02:27.016 --> 02:29.932
I talked to her for 15 minutes,
it cost me 800 dollars!

02:29.975 --> 02:32.456
- You know how much
a criminal lawyer costs?

02:32.500 --> 02:35.198
- I need this payday;
we didn't get the last one.

02:35.242 --> 02:36.460
- We all need it.

02:36.504 --> 02:37.896
But let's not
be stupid about it.

02:37.940 --> 02:39.942
- What's stupid
is if we screw this up.

02:39.985 --> 02:42.727
Because Gang Friend is not
going to give us another shot.

02:42.771 --> 02:44.076
- Gang friend?

02:44.120 --> 02:45.252
- Probably some
teenagers, like,

02:45.295 --> 02:46.818
stole an Xbox
or something.

02:46.862 --> 02:49.691
I promise you, it was nothing.
- It wasn't nothing!

02:49.734 --> 02:53.477
It was the FBI.
- Okay, so it was two Xboxes.

02:53.521 --> 02:56.088
- Freeze, ladies.
[all gasp]

02:56.132 --> 02:57.438
- Huh?
- Whoa, hey.

02:57.481 --> 03:00.005
Look at you.
- Huh? What's up, y'all.

03:00.049 --> 03:01.659
- Hey.
- [laughs]

03:01.703 --> 03:03.922
- First day as an
officer in training.

03:03.966 --> 03:05.315
- Mm-hmm.
Now tell me,

03:05.359 --> 03:06.490
would you pull over
if you saw all this

03:06.534 --> 03:07.796
coming at you
in the rearview?

03:07.839 --> 03:09.537
- Oh, I'd pay the
ticket on the spot.

03:09.580 --> 03:11.626
- I mean, I'd run, but you'd
catch me in five seconds.

03:11.669 --> 03:13.715
- Hear that?
Getting real now, huh?

03:13.758 --> 03:16.718
- Oh yeah,
realer by the minute.

03:23.246 --> 03:25.944
- What about sun block?
- Nancy has the spray kind.

03:25.988 --> 03:27.859
- I guess if you can
afford to go to Hawaii,

03:27.903 --> 03:29.209
you can afford the spray kind.

03:29.252 --> 03:30.775
- Don't eat just
mac and cheese, okay?

03:30.819 --> 03:33.169
- I know how to make at least
two to five other dishes.

03:33.213 --> 03:34.866
- And set your alarm for work.

03:34.910 --> 03:38.696
- I am a fully functioning
adult human.

03:38.740 --> 03:44.049
- You're not good alone.
- I can take care of myself.

03:44.093 --> 03:46.356
I mean, sometimes.

03:46.400 --> 03:47.879
Okay, I love you,
I'm going to miss you.

03:47.923 --> 03:49.881
Have the best time,
I promise I will not call

03:49.925 --> 03:51.187
unless it's an emergency.

03:51.231 --> 03:52.493
- Okay.
- Okay?

03:52.536 --> 03:54.059
- All right.
- Okay, hey, love ya.

03:54.103 --> 03:55.235
- Love ya.

03:55.278 --> 03:57.846
both: Never put
no one above ya!

03:59.804 --> 04:02.242
- Miss you, miss you, bye.
- Miss you, okay.

04:02.285 --> 04:04.853
[soft music]

04:04.896 --> 04:06.507
♪

04:06.550 --> 04:10.598
- Well, am-scray, I'm like,
dying for some alone time.

04:10.641 --> 04:13.992
- I love you so much, Mom.
- I love you, baby.

04:14.036 --> 04:15.907
[kissing noises]

04:15.951 --> 04:17.039
- Bye!
- Bye!

04:17.082 --> 04:18.083
[higher pitches]
- Bye!

04:18.127 --> 04:21.304
- Bye!

04:21.348 --> 04:23.306
[groans]

04:28.877 --> 04:30.270
[sighs]

04:40.889 --> 04:42.194
- All right,
what if I just mark you down

04:42.238 --> 04:43.892
for like clean up or something?

04:43.935 --> 04:47.765
- I'd really love to, I just
don't have any time right now.

04:47.809 --> 04:51.116
- Oh, my God,
what happened to your car?

04:51.160 --> 04:54.772
- Oh, got Kenny a BB gun.

04:56.948 --> 04:59.386
- When did we
start this service?

04:59.429 --> 05:02.867
Anyway, think about it, B.
I'll call you.

05:02.911 --> 05:04.565
- Okay.

05:06.915 --> 05:11.963
What do you want?

05:12.007 --> 05:15.315
[funky music]

05:15.358 --> 05:22.496
♪

05:24.498 --> 05:26.630
- Careful with those snacks.

05:26.674 --> 05:30.112
I don't want to spend my
weekend cleaning up this car.

05:48.043 --> 05:49.653
- Yeah, I'm not sure
I see the problem.

05:49.697 --> 05:52.482
- You and me both, brother.
- Annie.

05:52.526 --> 05:53.831
- [scoffs]

05:53.875 --> 05:55.790
I just would like
to take this moment

05:55.833 --> 05:58.096
to personally thank you
for this opportunity.

05:58.140 --> 05:59.924
I promise you,
we're going to iron this out.

05:59.968 --> 06:02.231
We're going to make you proud.
- Okay, hold up, Annie.

06:02.274 --> 06:03.798
- Y'all asked
for a piece of this.

06:03.841 --> 06:05.843
- Yes, we did, sir.
That's true.

06:05.887 --> 06:07.671
- That was before
the FBI dropped by.

06:07.715 --> 06:09.412
- Okay, let's just
calm down, sorry.

06:09.456 --> 06:11.719
She just kind of does this,
it's all part of the process.

06:11.762 --> 06:13.373
- What is that
supposed to mean?

06:13.416 --> 06:16.071
- Hmm, I don't know, you
begged our parents for a piano,

06:16.114 --> 06:18.813
and they dropped
three grand on a baby upright.

06:18.856 --> 06:21.598
And guess who decides
she'd rather play violin?

06:21.642 --> 06:23.078
- I'm staying out of it.

06:23.121 --> 06:24.993
- It sounds like y'all
got a lot to work out.

06:25.036 --> 06:26.690
So...
- Wait, wait, wait, wait,

06:26.734 --> 06:28.779
wait a second, don't you
want to take your product?

06:32.740 --> 06:34.698
- This ain't the Girl Scouts.

06:34.742 --> 06:36.308
You can't give
the cookies back.

06:36.352 --> 06:38.963
- Aren't you worried
about the FBI?

06:39.007 --> 06:41.226
- Nah.
- See?

06:41.270 --> 06:42.793
- There's a
distribution system.

06:42.837 --> 06:44.708
You've been distributed to.

06:44.752 --> 06:46.449
- What--what does that mean?

06:46.493 --> 06:48.408
- It means
you're on the hook now.

06:48.451 --> 06:52.716
- It's like, 100 grand.
- Oh, you don't got to wash it.

06:52.760 --> 06:54.849
- Then what do we do with it?

06:54.892 --> 06:58.069
- Burn it, eat it,
wipe your ass with it.

06:58.113 --> 06:59.506
And then write me a check.

06:59.549 --> 07:01.551
Because either way,
I'm coming to collect.

07:01.595 --> 07:02.944
- Hey.

07:02.987 --> 07:06.295
Guess who ended up
taking the piano lessons?

07:06.338 --> 07:09.254
Six years.
It's gonna be fine.

07:09.298 --> 07:11.909
[soft pop music]

07:11.953 --> 07:13.476
♪

07:13.520 --> 07:15.086
[clears throat]

07:15.130 --> 07:16.914
[door opens]

07:16.958 --> 07:18.002
What?

07:18.046 --> 07:19.569
- Okay, the pins
represent the stores

07:19.613 --> 07:21.441
with the biggest ticket items.

07:21.484 --> 07:25.270
We've got blue for electronics,
yellow for appliances--

07:25.314 --> 07:27.359
- Is this the same map
you used for Black Friday?

07:27.403 --> 07:28.970
- Yes, but I expanded it,

07:29.013 --> 07:32.016
because it is way too risky
to shop locally right now.

07:32.060 --> 07:33.975
- Damn, you really upped
your crafting game, Martha.

07:34.018 --> 07:36.934
- Hey, hey.
There is a system.

07:36.978 --> 07:38.501
I am trying to
keep us organized

07:38.545 --> 07:40.808
so that we don't get caught.

07:40.851 --> 07:42.984
- Okay...
- What if they test the bills?

07:43.027 --> 07:46.466
I once saw a guy at 7/11
get straight up tased.

07:46.509 --> 07:48.685
- Well, at least
he wasn't arrested.

07:48.729 --> 07:50.339
- And then he got arrested.

07:50.382 --> 07:53.298
- I used a security pen
from work on one of the 20's.

07:53.342 --> 07:54.778
We're not
getting tased or arrested.

07:54.822 --> 07:57.041
This cash is
[kissing noise] primo.

07:57.085 --> 07:59.783
- The red bands
are the fake money.

07:59.827 --> 08:02.307
So when you make a return,
you put on a green band.

08:02.351 --> 08:06.486
And you keep it separate.
- Red goes out, green comes in.

08:06.529 --> 08:07.965
- Just like Christmas.

08:08.009 --> 08:11.099
- This is who we are now, huh?

08:11.142 --> 08:12.535
- I mean...

08:12.579 --> 08:14.189
desperate times.

08:14.232 --> 08:16.539
- We can do this.

08:16.583 --> 08:19.411
We're just
normal women, shopping.

08:19.455 --> 08:21.762
- With money to burn, baby!

08:21.805 --> 08:24.982
[Jungle's "Busy Earnin'"]

08:25.026 --> 08:32.033
♪

08:43.871 --> 08:45.742
- All right, you saved $5.21.

08:45.786 --> 08:47.439
- Thanks a lot.
- Have a good one.

08:47.483 --> 08:49.964
Next.

08:50.007 --> 08:52.706
- ♪ So you've come
a long way ♪

08:52.749 --> 08:54.838
- Find everything okay?
- Yeah.

08:54.882 --> 08:57.058
- ♪ But you're never
out late ♪

08:57.101 --> 09:00.583
- [soft laugh]

09:00.627 --> 09:01.845
[beep]

09:01.889 --> 09:04.326
- ♪ It's crime

09:04.369 --> 09:06.241
♪ Too busy earning

09:06.284 --> 09:08.548
- Couldn't decide.

09:08.591 --> 09:10.375
- I see that.

09:10.419 --> 09:13.683
- $4,822.38.

09:13.727 --> 09:20.995
♪

09:29.612 --> 09:32.746
[machine beeps, flitters]

09:33.268 --> 09:34.443
- Wha--what's that?

09:34.486 --> 09:36.619
- We have to check
our large bills.

09:36.663 --> 09:39.013
- You guys don't
use the pen thingy?

09:39.056 --> 09:41.189
- No, not anymore.
Those never really worked.

09:41.232 --> 09:43.104
- You know what?
I'm actually in a hurry.

09:43.147 --> 09:46.673
I'm just gonna come back.
- This will just take a second.

09:46.716 --> 09:49.763
- ♪ And I get it always

09:49.806 --> 09:52.592
- So we just finished
this major remodel, right?

09:52.635 --> 09:54.811
Tear the kitchen
right down to the studs.

09:54.855 --> 09:57.422
So I can buy
all new appliances.

09:57.466 --> 09:58.859
Fun, right?

09:58.902 --> 10:00.817
Only not fun,
because the appliances

10:00.861 --> 10:03.820
don't match the counters,
and now I gotta buy

10:03.864 --> 10:05.343
all new colors to try out.

10:05.387 --> 10:06.649
First up was eggshell.

10:06.693 --> 10:08.216
What the hell
kind of color is eggshell?

10:08.259 --> 10:10.871
I'll tell you what kind.
It's white, just plain white.

10:10.914 --> 10:13.134
So then I tried seashell,
and I don't know if y'all

10:13.177 --> 10:15.484
have ever been to
the sea and seen a shell.

10:15.527 --> 10:16.746
You might need a vacation,

10:16.790 --> 10:19.836
but I assure you,
that ain't it.

10:19.880 --> 10:22.752
And don't even
get me started on corn silk.

10:22.796 --> 10:24.624
That is nonsense--

10:24.667 --> 10:26.756
- I need a manager
to the front please.

10:26.800 --> 10:29.629
Manager to the front.

10:30.804 --> 10:34.329
[machine ticking]

10:39.595 --> 10:41.031
- Is there a problem?

10:41.075 --> 10:42.816
- ♪ You can't get enough

10:42.859 --> 10:45.427
♪

10:45.470 --> 10:48.648
[machine ticking]

10:48.691 --> 10:50.867
[beeping]

10:50.911 --> 10:54.001
- Great.
Everything looks good.

10:54.044 --> 10:56.656
You want your
receipt in the bag?

10:56.699 --> 10:58.701
- Uh, no, I'll hold onto it.

10:58.745 --> 11:00.050
- There you go.

11:00.094 --> 11:03.401
- You want all this
back on a card?

11:03.445 --> 11:05.142
- Cash is fine.

11:05.186 --> 11:06.970
[beep]

11:07.014 --> 11:09.799
- ♪ Too busy earning

11:09.843 --> 11:10.800
♪ You can't get enough

11:10.844 --> 11:14.717
♪

11:14.761 --> 11:19.461
♪ Just busy earning

11:19.504 --> 11:20.854
♪ You can't get enough

11:20.897 --> 11:22.159
♪ No

11:22.203 --> 11:24.466
♪

11:24.509 --> 11:28.862
♪ Just busy earning

11:28.905 --> 11:30.472
♪ You can't get enough

11:30.515 --> 11:34.694
- Did you get the verifier?
- This shizz is good.

11:39.786 --> 11:42.702
[indistinct chatter]

11:45.008 --> 11:47.228
- Do you play games?

11:47.271 --> 11:49.404
- Uh, you know,
I'm actually in the market for

11:49.447 --> 11:51.841
something more like
a flat screen type deal.

11:51.885 --> 11:53.190
Something kind
of stupidly pricy.

11:53.234 --> 11:55.018
- Price doesn't
always equal quality.

11:55.062 --> 11:57.020
- You're talking to an
irresponsible millennial here.

11:57.064 --> 12:00.154
- Uh, well in that case,
our 4K ultra high defs

12:00.197 --> 12:02.199
are rated the best.
- Mmm.

12:02.243 --> 12:04.245
- But they run upwards
of four grand, so.

12:04.288 --> 12:07.509
- [whistles]
- Yeah, steep.

12:07.552 --> 12:09.206
- Ouch, well.

12:09.250 --> 12:11.818
I guess I should
only get four then.

12:14.081 --> 12:16.170
- Four.

12:16.213 --> 12:16.997
TVs?

12:17.040 --> 12:18.476
- What do you think, five?

12:18.520 --> 12:19.826
- I don't know, I mean,
are you messing with me?

12:19.869 --> 12:21.131
[both laugh]
- No!

12:21.175 --> 12:22.393
Why would I
be messing with you?

12:22.437 --> 12:23.830
- Nobody that looks like you

12:23.873 --> 12:25.788
would ever be that good
for my commission.

12:25.832 --> 12:27.790
- And what do I look like?

12:27.834 --> 12:29.574
- Uh, you know, hot?

12:29.618 --> 12:32.403
- Okay, man, you know what, you
got this whole thing all wrong.

12:32.447 --> 12:36.190
- Okay, you're not hot?
- No, no, I'm hot, obviously.

12:36.233 --> 12:40.672
I'm just serious about the TVs,
I'm not messing with you.

12:40.716 --> 12:42.762
- Ringing up the hottie!

12:42.805 --> 12:44.198
- [soft laugh]

13:09.832 --> 13:11.921
- [gasps]
Okay, creeper.

13:11.965 --> 13:13.183
- You just getting home now?

13:13.227 --> 13:14.794
- You don't have
to wait up for me.

13:14.837 --> 13:16.143
- I'm surprised
you can see straight

13:16.186 --> 13:17.927
with all these doubles
you've been pulling.

13:17.971 --> 13:20.234
- I mean, it's hard to say no
to the extra shifts.

13:20.277 --> 13:22.062
- Yeah.
- How was rehearsal?

13:22.105 --> 13:24.455
- Ah, Sara seemed
a little tired.

13:24.499 --> 13:26.544
- Is she okay?
- She said she was.

13:26.588 --> 13:28.677
- Oh, by the way,

13:28.720 --> 13:30.984
our little girl,
she's got my moves.

13:31.027 --> 13:32.507
No, dude, she was like--

13:32.550 --> 13:37.251
[grunts]
Ay, ay, ay, ay!

13:37.294 --> 13:38.948
- Okay, if those are her moves,

13:38.992 --> 13:40.558
We need to take her
off that dance team.

13:40.602 --> 13:45.302
- Oh, come on now.
You remember what it was.

13:45.346 --> 13:47.522
- [groans]
I need to get off my feet.

13:47.565 --> 13:49.306
- Oh, we could do that too.
- [sighs]

13:49.350 --> 13:53.180
- Hey, hey, where--
where's your uniform?

13:53.223 --> 13:56.487
- Oh, um, I left it at work.

13:56.531 --> 14:00.491
It's covered in
ketchup and frustration.

14:00.535 --> 14:01.884
- That's nasty.

14:01.928 --> 14:03.538
[both laugh]
- You don't even know.

14:03.581 --> 14:04.887
- I don't even care.

14:04.931 --> 14:08.238
[vocalizing]

14:08.282 --> 14:10.937
- Oh, you, you want to--
- Come on, all right?

14:10.980 --> 14:12.852
- Oh, you didn't--
- Hey, oh.

14:12.895 --> 14:14.941
both: Oh!

14:14.984 --> 14:16.290
- Yes.

14:16.333 --> 14:18.858
- 19,685 bucks.

