30:03.845 --> 30:06.848
- So what do I say?
- To whom?

30:06.892 --> 30:10.199
- The FBI.
What do I tell them?

30:10.243 --> 30:12.985
- They ain't got nothing.
- They've got a picture of you.

30:13.028 --> 30:16.858
- That ain't special.
I'm on Facebook, too.

30:16.902 --> 30:18.947
Your cut.

30:18.991 --> 30:20.688
- Wait, wait, wait.

30:22.429 --> 30:24.561
- Listen.

30:24.605 --> 30:26.172
In my line of work,

30:26.215 --> 30:28.087
If you don't have
the FBI on your back,

30:28.130 --> 30:30.132
you ain't making noise.

30:30.176 --> 30:31.917
- I don't want to make noise.

30:31.960 --> 30:33.788
They're gonna want to know
what someone like me

30:33.832 --> 30:36.791
is doing with someone like you.

30:36.835 --> 30:40.012
- What are you doing
with someone like me?

30:41.491 --> 30:44.059
- Well, obviously,
I can't tell them that.

30:44.103 --> 30:47.280
- Right, right.

30:47.323 --> 30:49.064
All right, so tell them
I was hitting it.

30:49.108 --> 30:50.631
- What?

30:50.674 --> 30:54.983
- Oh, sorry, sweetheart.
Tell them we're making love.

30:58.726 --> 31:02.295
- I--
how do I even say that?

31:02.338 --> 31:05.602
- [laughs]
You'll think of something.

31:05.646 --> 31:07.996
Make me sound
good though, yeah?

31:09.911 --> 31:10.999
[car door shuts]

31:15.438 --> 31:16.875
- [soft scoff]

31:20.269 --> 31:22.924
- I was feeling better.

31:22.968 --> 31:25.448
So I was saving it
until I needed it again.

31:25.492 --> 31:27.320
- That's not how
medicine works, baby

31:27.363 --> 31:29.931
- Yeah, I thought you were
supposed to be honor roll here.

31:29.975 --> 31:32.499
- Now we're going to have to
take that bumper sticker off.

31:32.542 --> 31:34.022
[soft laugh]

31:35.632 --> 31:38.505
- I wanted to try
and help you guys out.

31:38.548 --> 31:40.942
- Help us out with what?

31:40.986 --> 31:42.683
- Like, money and stuff.

31:42.726 --> 31:46.861
I know we can't afford it.

31:46.905 --> 31:47.993
- Well...

31:48.036 --> 31:50.865
there's something
you don't know.

31:52.736 --> 31:54.347
Should we tell her?

31:54.390 --> 31:57.611
- I don't know,
you think she can handle it?

31:57.654 --> 31:59.961
- The truth is...

32:00.005 --> 32:01.571
we are...

32:01.615 --> 32:03.008
stinking rich.

32:03.051 --> 32:07.316
I'm talking stacks
on stacks on stacks, loaded.

32:07.360 --> 32:09.710
- We are rolling in it.

32:09.753 --> 32:13.105
- And the truth, my dear,
is that you are...

32:13.148 --> 32:15.281
wait for it--

32:15.324 --> 32:16.630
royalty.

32:16.673 --> 32:18.893
♪ Mm-hmm

32:18.937 --> 32:20.373
We didn't want you
to grow up spoiled.

32:20.416 --> 32:21.896
That's why we kept it
on the DL.

32:21.940 --> 32:24.551
- Mm-hmm.
- This is like a bad movie.

32:24.594 --> 32:26.205
- It's why
we bought the tiniest,

32:26.248 --> 32:27.684
cheapest house we could find.

32:27.728 --> 32:30.252
- Oh--oh--okay.
Hold--it's not that bad.

32:30.296 --> 32:32.559
- Oh, and that
explains the car.

32:32.602 --> 32:33.908
- Exactly.
- Wait a second.

32:33.952 --> 32:36.041
What's wrong with my car?
- And the food.

32:36.084 --> 32:38.608
- Now that makes sense.
- Hey, watch yourself.

32:38.652 --> 32:41.568
[gentle music]

32:41.611 --> 32:43.787
Baby, don't worry about us.

32:43.831 --> 32:47.878
Just go to school,
and play, and be a kid.

32:47.922 --> 32:49.271
- That's it.

32:49.315 --> 32:52.100
- And swallow your damn pills
from now on, okay?

32:52.144 --> 32:53.623
- Okay, Mommy.

32:53.667 --> 32:58.933
♪

32:58.977 --> 33:00.935
- All the stuff you think
you're keeping from them?

33:00.979 --> 33:03.198
You're not.

33:03.242 --> 33:04.939
- Don't go there.
- [sighs]

33:04.983 --> 33:07.376
- I mean, I'm not going to say
that I'm a bad mother...

33:07.420 --> 33:08.943
- Oh, she's going there.

33:08.987 --> 33:12.120
- I could have
paid more attention.

33:12.164 --> 33:15.254
- You do the best you can.

33:15.297 --> 33:17.604
- [sniffs]

33:22.870 --> 33:25.090
[sniffs]
Those better be doughnuts.

33:25.133 --> 33:29.007
Do not come at me with some
wack-ass cheese Danish.

33:32.314 --> 33:36.449
[soft music]

33:36.492 --> 33:39.626
Those aren't doughnuts.

33:39.669 --> 33:42.063
- It's everything,
it's our whole cut.

33:42.107 --> 33:43.891
- We knew you'd need it
for the hospital bill.

33:43.934 --> 33:46.546
- We don't want you to even
think about it, okay?

33:46.589 --> 33:52.595
♪

33:52.639 --> 33:55.598
- And messed up my damn face.

33:55.642 --> 33:57.818
- It was already
pretty messed up.

33:57.861 --> 34:01.691
- I hate you guys.
- We know.

34:04.085 --> 34:08.437
- So, have you already
discussed the comment

34:08.481 --> 34:11.440
about the twigs and the--
- Ah, yes.

34:11.484 --> 34:13.964
Yes, we--
we had a discussion about it.

34:14.008 --> 34:16.706
- Man, I missed it?
- Mm-hmm.

34:16.750 --> 34:18.665
I was the bigger man,
I apologized.

34:18.708 --> 34:20.580
- Yeah, sort of.

34:20.623 --> 34:23.104
- Well, I said it wasn't
my finest moment.

34:23.148 --> 34:25.150
- You also said it
could have been way worse.

34:25.193 --> 34:27.848
- Yeah, because I wanted
to say "raisin cave."

34:27.891 --> 34:30.720
But I restrained myself.
- What does that even mean?

34:30.764 --> 34:33.941
- Uh, I think I know.
And it is not an apology.

34:33.984 --> 34:36.335
- [laughs]
What you want from me, blood?

34:36.378 --> 34:38.119
Please.

34:38.163 --> 34:41.514
- [wheezing laughing]
Raisin cave.

34:41.557 --> 34:44.038
- [laughing]
I mean...

34:44.082 --> 34:45.561
- Oh, my God!

34:45.605 --> 34:49.870
[all laughing]

34:53.526 --> 34:53.917
.

34:53.961 --> 34:55.876
- Hi.
- Can I help you?

34:55.919 --> 34:56.920
- Yeah, I'd like to fill out
one of those

34:56.964 --> 34:58.313
customer complaint cards.

34:58.357 --> 35:00.315
It's about my recent
in-home hookup.

35:00.359 --> 35:01.882
- Oh, a comment card.

35:01.925 --> 35:03.536
- Well, all my
comments are complaints,

35:03.579 --> 35:07.192
but call it what you want to.
- Absolutely, no problem.

35:07.235 --> 35:09.803
Overall, how happy were you
with your service?

35:09.846 --> 35:11.892
- Un.
Very unhappy.

35:11.935 --> 35:13.459
- Uh, one through ten?

35:13.502 --> 35:18.855
- Mmm, like a negative six.
- Absolutely, no problem.

35:18.899 --> 35:23.077
And was your service performed
in a timely manner?

35:23.121 --> 35:25.732
- If by timely, you mean
like a little woodpecker,

35:25.775 --> 35:30.476
then yeah.
- Absolutely, no problem.

35:30.519 --> 35:33.435
Was the job completed
to your satisfaction?

35:33.479 --> 35:36.090
- Uh, no, I was
definitely not satisfied.

35:36.134 --> 35:39.920
- He didn't finish?
- Oh, he finished.

35:39.963 --> 35:42.270
- I am so sorry
about your experience.

35:42.314 --> 35:44.707
We take our customer feedback
very seriously.

35:44.751 --> 35:48.276
- Now, how seriously is that?
Do you dock people's pay?

35:48.320 --> 35:49.930
- I--
- Do you fire them?

35:49.973 --> 35:51.453
Because I'd hate
to see that happen.

35:51.497 --> 35:55.327
- If the situation were
extreme enough, certainly.

35:55.370 --> 35:58.243
You didn't happen to catch
your technician's name?

35:58.286 --> 35:59.940
- You know, he just
wasn't that memorable.

35:59.983 --> 36:03.117
He kinda had, like--
like, a mini dad bod.

36:03.161 --> 36:06.425
And he smelled like, hmm,
it's hard to describe.

36:06.468 --> 36:09.689
Have you ever been
to a zoo in the rain?

36:09.732 --> 36:11.734
- Mm-mm.
- Oh!

36:11.778 --> 36:13.910
There he is.

36:17.087 --> 36:20.221
- Wait, you're Nicole?
- Mm-hmm.

36:20.265 --> 36:22.789
- He actually talked
a lot of smack about you, too.

36:22.832 --> 36:24.486
Just saying.

36:28.751 --> 36:30.188
[door opens]

36:30.927 --> 36:33.103
- Hey.
[door shuts]

36:34.975 --> 36:36.324
- Oh, wow, you cooked?

36:36.368 --> 36:38.413
- Yeah, I watched
that Rachel Ray show.

36:38.457 --> 36:40.198
There's something wrong
with that woman.

36:40.241 --> 36:43.244
She's like, so happy.
- I know, it's really weird.

36:43.288 --> 36:46.160
- Yeah, hey, do you want me
to heat up your plate?

36:46.204 --> 36:48.162
- Sara's in the hospital again.

36:48.206 --> 36:51.470
I'm going to shower
and then head back there.

36:51.513 --> 36:54.212
- All right, hey, Beth.

36:54.255 --> 36:57.302
I'm really, really trying here.

36:57.345 --> 36:59.739
- I know.

36:59.782 --> 37:01.828
- You think I could fix it?

37:01.871 --> 37:04.309
- I think it's
going to take more than

37:04.352 --> 37:06.572
filling up the car
and Rachel Ray.

37:06.615 --> 37:09.662
- Right.

37:09.705 --> 37:11.577
If it never happened.

37:11.620 --> 37:14.319
You know, Amber, the money.

37:14.362 --> 37:17.974
Would you still be with me?

37:18.018 --> 37:21.282
- I don't even know
how to answer that.

37:24.981 --> 37:27.070
- I think you just did.

37:37.559 --> 37:42.521
- Mrs. Boland, can I
get you anything? Coffee?

37:42.564 --> 37:45.393
- Oh, uh, you drink coffee
at this hour?

37:45.437 --> 37:48.396
- I don't sleep much anyway.
You?

37:48.440 --> 37:50.659
- I had an affair.

37:50.703 --> 37:52.139
- You had an affair.

37:52.182 --> 37:54.968
- I'm not proud of it,
and it's over now.

37:55.011 --> 37:56.535
But that's why
he was at the house,

37:56.578 --> 37:58.885
and that's why
I couldn't say anything

37:58.928 --> 38:01.366
in front of my husband
and my children.

38:01.409 --> 38:02.889
- Oh.

38:02.932 --> 38:05.021
Well.

38:05.065 --> 38:07.241
Okay, then.

38:07.285 --> 38:11.201
- Okay.
- Okay.

38:11.245 --> 38:14.379
Just out of curiosity,
where'd you meet him?

38:19.601 --> 38:21.386
I'm just wondering
where a nice lady like you

38:21.429 --> 38:23.518
meets an inner-city gangbanger.
PTA?

38:23.562 --> 38:25.172
Or is it like,
a speed dating thing?

38:25.215 --> 38:27.914
What's that website,
It's Just Lunch?

38:27.957 --> 38:30.090
- At a bar.
- What was he wearing?

38:30.133 --> 38:31.570
- Jeans.
- What about you?

38:31.613 --> 38:34.355
- A dress.
- Where'd you meet him?

38:34.399 --> 38:36.488
- At a restaurant.
- You just said bar.

38:36.531 --> 38:39.099
- A bar-restaurant.
They had food.

38:39.142 --> 38:40.709
- What was the name?

38:40.753 --> 38:42.015
- Lucky's.

38:42.058 --> 38:43.799
- Bet they'd remember
a pair like you.

38:43.843 --> 38:45.235
Who drove?

38:45.279 --> 38:48.064
You or him, who drove?
- Um, we both did.

38:48.108 --> 38:49.936
- What kind of car
does he drive?

38:49.979 --> 38:51.851
- Black BMW.

38:51.894 --> 38:53.113
- It'd be registered,
I'll check it.

38:53.156 --> 38:56.203
- It might be a Cadillac.
- Maybe.

38:59.467 --> 39:02.209
Have a good night,
Mrs. Boland.

39:03.819 --> 39:06.996
[keys clacking]

39:13.786 --> 39:15.309
- It was a one-night stand.

39:15.353 --> 39:17.050
I had just found out
that my husband

39:17.093 --> 39:19.487
was cheating on me
with a child.

39:19.531 --> 39:21.228
More or less.

39:21.271 --> 39:25.363
And I was lonely, and angry.

39:25.406 --> 39:27.190
And...

39:27.234 --> 39:29.062
normally, sleeping with
a complete stranger

39:29.105 --> 39:30.803
would repulse me.

39:30.846 --> 39:33.196
But it didn't that day.

39:33.240 --> 39:35.024
I dropped the kids off
at school,

39:35.068 --> 39:37.984
and I went straight to the bar.

39:38.027 --> 39:39.464
- Where was your husband?

39:39.507 --> 39:43.424
- Screwing his secretary
and losing all our money.

39:43.468 --> 39:45.687
- Fair enough.

39:45.731 --> 39:48.429
- We drank a little.

39:48.473 --> 39:51.171
And I invited him
back to my house.

39:51.214 --> 39:54.217
We drank a little more.

39:54.261 --> 39:58.700
And then I realized that
what I was doing was insane.

39:58.744 --> 40:00.702
And I told him to go.

40:03.183 --> 40:05.838
And he kissed me.

40:05.881 --> 40:08.797
I kissed him back.

40:08.841 --> 40:10.799
He pulled my panties down,

40:10.843 --> 40:13.367
and we screwed right
on the kitchen table,

40:13.411 --> 40:16.675
on the breakfast dishes.

40:16.718 --> 40:19.155
The kids had pancakes.

40:19.199 --> 40:20.722
Blueberry.

40:20.766 --> 40:22.245
If you were wondering.

40:22.289 --> 40:24.422
[Phantogram's "Cruel World"]

40:24.465 --> 40:27.033
It only happened once.

40:27.076 --> 40:30.558
And I've never seen
that man again.

40:30.602 --> 40:32.517
And I don't plan to.

40:32.560 --> 40:35.389
♪

40:35.433 --> 40:37.435
- ♪ I'm putting you
out of your misery ♪

40:37.478 --> 40:39.698
- Thank you for coming in.

40:39.741 --> 40:41.482
♪

40:41.526 --> 40:46.052
- ♪ 'Cause darling
you're dragging me down ♪

40:46.095 --> 40:47.619
- Mrs. Boland?

40:47.662 --> 40:51.405
- ♪ I wish I could say
that I'm sorry ♪

40:51.449 --> 40:54.452
- Just be careful
who you bring into your home.

40:54.495 --> 40:56.497
- I'm tougher than I look.

40:56.541 --> 40:58.891
- ♪ It's a cruel cruel world

40:58.934 --> 41:02.677
♪

41:02.721 --> 41:05.288
♪ So I'm saying my goodbyes

41:05.332 --> 41:08.509
♪

41:08.553 --> 41:10.859
♪ Goodbye to my good side

41:10.903 --> 41:14.428
♪

41:14.472 --> 41:17.518
♪ It only ever got me hurt

41:17.562 --> 41:20.434
♪ And I finally learned

41:20.478 --> 41:22.915
♪ It's a cruel cruel world

41:22.958 --> 41:30.226
♪
